            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A conventional target containing a supply of 5 litres",
                " of liquid helium was used.  During the first  series",
                " of  measurements  the  target  cell  was  a vertical",
                " cylinder with 50 micron mylar walls and  a  diameter",
                " of  6  cm;  in  the  second  series  the  cell was a",
                " horizontal cylinder with a length of  6  cm  in  the",
                " beam  direction,  a  diameter  of 3 cm and 50 micron",
                " kapton walls."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "P"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "T"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Because the  small variation of the proton and triton",
                " laboratory angles with photon  energy  for  a  given",
                " c.m.s. angle the direct measurement of cross section",
                " was able."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": 5.0,
                "maximum_value": 11.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Systematic  errors  were estimated",
                " to be about of 5 - 11%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The corrections were made for loss  of  particles  by",
                " inelastic  nuclear  interactions (from 8 to 30%) and",
                " for background (1 - 8%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The He-4(g,p)H-3  reaction  was  investigated  in the",
                " photon energy region between 200 and 450 MeV and  at",
                " proton c.m.  angles between 30 and 150 degrees.  The",
                " outgoing particles were detected in  coincidence  in",
                " two   time-of-flight   spectrometers  consisting  of",
                " scintillation counters;  energies and angles of both",
                " particles  were  determined.  The  measured  angular",
                " distributions  show  a  strong  forward  peak.   The",
                " differential  cross  sections  and  the  total cross",
                " section fall smoothly with increasing photon energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
